[
  {
    "startTime": 4.209,
    "endTime": 5.678999999999999,
    "text": "Hey, what's up everyone?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 5.679,
    "endTime": 9.679,
    "text": "We are going to change it up a little bit today. We are going to"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 9.679,
    "endTime": 11.789,
    "text": "do a little experiment on local Americans,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 12.463,
    "endTime": 16.463,
    "text": "seeing how they respond to the question \"How are you?\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 17.095,
    "endTime": 21.465,
    "text": "Back in middle school, during English classes, you were taught to say,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 22.166,
    "endTime": 23.806,
    "text": "\"I'm fine thank you and you?\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 23.806,
    "endTime": 26.276,
    "text": "when you were asked \"How are you?\""
  },
  {
    "startTime": 26.883,
    "endTime": 29.163,
    "text": "But only recently, it's been pointed out that"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 29.163,
    "endTime": 32.643,
    "text": "no native speakers respond that way, but is that really true?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 33.205,
    "endTime": 36.495,
    "text": "Then, how DO they respond?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 37.266,
    "endTime": 40.736,
    "text": "I'm good. I'm great. I'm OK."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 40.844,
    "endTime": 44.424,
    "text": "I asked \"How are you?\" to 12 Americans"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 44.424,
    "endTime": 45.924,
    "text": "who live in L.A."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 46.284,
    "endTime": 51.304,
    "text": "Note that the Americans who were asked the question were not told what the question was beforehand,"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 51.375,
    "endTime": 53.685,
    "text": "so the response should come out pretty natural."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 53.868,
    "endTime": 57.868,
    "text": "I have gotten some unexpected responce."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 58.592,
    "endTime": 62.592,
    "text": "Let's see how Americans respond to the question \"How are you?\""
  },
